I saw my brothers get angry when they lost, or felt like they were treated unfairly when they didn't win.  I saw them throw things in anger.  I stopped wanting to play games because they always ended this way.

Now I try to teach my kids that there are more important things in life than winning or being right, that their relationship with their family is more important than that.  When they compete, they get angry with each other and walk away from whatever they were working on.  When I see them working together, they smile, laugh, and actually successfully finish whatever they are doing.
